# AI Feature Agent

## AI Question Framework

Defined in `shared/aiQuestions.ts` — the core of Thap's AI assistant based on master's thesis research.

### Structure
- **3 lifecycle stages**: Discovery (pre-purchase), Ownership, End-of-Life
- **8 universal categories**: Product info, Quality & materials, Price & value, Usage & maintenance, Compatibility, Warranty & support, Sustainability, Resale & reuse
- **Domain-specific sets**: Electronics, Clothing & Footwear, Furniture & Tools, Vehicles & Bicycles
- **50+ pre-defined questions** — contextual based on ownership status and product category

### Adding Questions
1. Add to appropriate section in `shared/aiQuestions.ts`
2. Tag with lifecycle stage and category
3. Include product domain if domain-specific
4. Test filtering logic in `server/aiQuestions.test.ts`

## AI Provider Architecture

### Current Providers
- ChatGPT (OpenAI API)
- Gemini (Google AI)
- Perplexity
- DeepSeek
- Built-in Forge API (Manus platform)

### "Bring Your Own Key" Model
- Users configure API keys in `ai_provider_settings` table
- Keys stored per-user, per-provider with `isActive` flag
- **Known adoption risk**: <5% of consumer users will configure API keys (see ARCHITECTURAL_COMPARISON.md)
- Future: consider embedded server-side key with freemium model

### AI Chat Procedure
- `ai.chat` procedure in `routers.ts`
- Takes: message, productId (optional), provider, conversation history
- Returns: AI response with markdown formatting
- Conversations persisted in `ai_conversations` table

## Guidelines

- AI responses render as markdown — ensure markdown rendering is safe (no XSS)
- Product context (name, brand, category, metadata) should be included in system prompt
- Respect token limits per provider
- Handle API errors gracefully (invalid key, rate limit, timeout) with user-friendly messages
- Never log full AI API keys — mask all but last 4 characters
